Description:
The platform and App aim to provide a fast, effective and convenient manner of various services to the citizens. A more secure and cost-effective means to access a full range of payments and financial services that serves both the constituents of the City and temporary inhabitants.

The mobile application has the following features:
- City of Manila’s Real Property and Business Tax Payments;
- Wide range of facilities for payment of bills for government and private entities;
- E-Wallet for loading, payment, sending and receiving of funds;

During the early stages of COVID-19 it evolved from an app-based tax payment and business registration into a platform addressing social inclusion by targeting vulnerable groups. The adoption and uptake of residents in the Go! Manila ecosystem is still slow compared to the number of projected registration, but the City is working on education and sensitization campaigns.

The Global Registry of Fossil Fuels addresses the issue of limited publicly accessible data to assess how much coal, oil and gas is being produced, where this production is occurring, or how it impacts the remaining carbon budget. The same gap in data exists for fossil fuel reserves. Information on reserves is typically held by private companies, and greenhouse gas emissions associated with global reserves vary widely based on a range of different methodologies.

The registry addresses this data gap by creating a centralised tool for transparency on fossil fuel supply. It brings together thousands of government and corporate data sources into one place in a fully open source manner, from the global right down to the individual project level.

The Global Registry converts this data into its carbon dioxide equivalent, using a first-of-its-kind, rigorously peer reviewed, open source CO2 emissions model that is able to provide a reliable assessment of the amount of CO2 embedded in fossil fuel production based on the unique features of each country.

The Global Registry:
- Aggregates data into a comprehensive open-source database, drawing from government and private-sector sources;
- Includes both country-level and project level data - project-level is important as this is where decision-making happens and liability is incurred;
- Integrates reserves, production, and emissions data with third-party scenarios to provide essential data for policymakers and others to make 1.5°C aligned production decisions;
- Includes life-cycle emissions from fossil fuel projects for both carbon dioxide and methane.
- Ranks countries based on absolute emissions and emissions intensities

Travelinsights.ai is an artificial intelligence (AI) tool to help improve the Armenia’s emerging tourism industry by gathering real-time perceptions of services and popular sites to bring evidence into policy-making. It is the world’s first AI-powered touristic tool that uses complex algorithms to detect, collect and analyze all the online reviews about Armenia. This way, it identifies the sources of tourist satisfaction and dissatisfaction during their stay in the country. Travelinsights.ai is the first attempt of Armenia National SDG Innovation Lab to bring evidence into policy-making.

As a data analytics product, the online tool collects, analyzes and categorizes tourist sentiments about Armenia expressed on popular travel websites, such as TripAdvisor and Booking.com, fuses travel storytelling and machine learning. The platform visualizes the results of sentiment analysis of over 174,000 touristic reviews about Armenia, scraped from Booking.com, TripAdvisor and Facebook.com, with disaggregation of 25 detailed aspects per 4 categories (hotel, restaurant, museum, landmark).

The tool helps governmental authorities to understand the tourist perception of Armenia as a touristic destination and develop an effective marketing strategy. When the user selects any options on the platform they can visualize results with the following level of granularity:
- Top 5 compliments and complaints as per each aspect;
- Tourist destinations by their type: hotel, restaurant, museum/landmark and attraction; 
- Insights and price timeline starting from the very first review of Armenia left online;
- Review and price heatmap;
- Separate detailed categories for different tourism spots.

With a view to achieving the vision for a paperless environment, the MoKloud platform provides storage space for every citizen for the safekeeping of personal official documents in a digitally secured format bearing a QR code and digital signature, as may be required. Currently, MoKloud hosts birth and marriage certificate extracts, digital vaccination passes, certificates of electricity supply and e-payslips. MoKloud documents are shared by API or scanned for verification.

MoKloud does the following:
(i) digitally empowers citizens by providing them with a storage space on the cloud to enable them to sign, access and share their official documents online;
(ii) eliminates the need for citizens to maintain physical government issued documents;
(iii) ensures authenticity of the documents and thereby eliminating usage of fake documents/certificates;
(iv) reduces administrative overhead of Government agencies, service delivery time and costs by enabling paperless transactions;
(v) ensures anytime, anywhere access to the documents by the citizens; and
(vi) provides secure and consented access of government issued documents to user agencies.

To date, 5 types of documents have been ported on MoKloud, namely, birth and marriage certificate extracts, digital vaccination passes, certificates of electricity supply and e-payslips, for a total of more than 500'000 documents. This figure is expected to grow considerably as more agencies become aware of the potential of the MoKloud platform.

Novelty:
1.	It has allowed CGU to expand its results, with more timeliness, in a more objective way, with lower costs, and with fewer people;
2.	It has allowed the automatic tracking of almost all purchases by the federal administration, which would have been impossible with humans;
3.	It allowed the intensive use of artificial intelligence algorithms and different databases from different sources to solve a problem of great relevance to the public administration;
4.	It is developed in a network at CGU, with the participation of professionals from different areas and different locations, according to their skills and regardless of their hierarchical location; and
5.	It inaugurated the official development of data science solutions by staff from the CGU's final areas, outside the IT area, which has boosted the construction of technological solutions using artificial intelligence.

Description:
The Simple Flight is aimed at air transport users (individuals and companies), scheduled and general aviation companies, airport operators, aircraft manufacturers, aircraft maintenance companies, air transport workers.

The innovative character of Voo Simples (Simple Flights) is demonstrated by its pioneering character in the regulatory context of the national civil aviation, its comprehensiveness if compared to other Regulatory Agencies, and the structural changes it has promoted.

The objectives of Simple Flights are 
- Continually seek the simplification and debureaucratization of ANAC's actions aiming to reduce administrative costs for airlines and travelers;
- Promote actions related to improving the effectiveness and efficiency of public services provided by the Agency;
- Promote the improvement of ANAC's interaction with the regulated ones;
- Increase the transparency and dissemination of actions and results obtained;
- Guarantee the appropriate treatment to contributions for improvement and simplification of processes forwarded to ANAC.

The Simple Flight program currently (August 2022) has 70 actions in its portfolio, of which 46 have been completed and 18 are in progress. In just 3 months after the program's launch, 27 of the 52 originally planned had already been delivered.

Impact & Results:
Through the launch of TV and Podcast Inovação Barueri, we increased the number of people reached by more than 1,618% and the interaction by more than 394%, this reflected directly on citizen information. 
The reach on social networks averaged 17K, and after the start of TV on 2/7/2020 the reach increased to over 67K. Regarding Facebook we had an average of 2,200 people/month, but after the launch of TV the reach was exponential, and went up to over 33,700 people. Other important metrics are: 
- + 528,000 interactions/impressions on social media; 
- + 200,000 social media reaches;
- + 147 thousand views on the YouTube channel of TV Inovação Barueri;
- + 109 guests have been through our programs;
- 440 programs carried out; 
- + 406 hours of public viewing only on Youtube 
- + 10 trainings in the process of being recorded by the team of trainees in the Talent Development program.

Novelty:
Gov4SAA program is an innovation since:
1) It is the first and only program that has engaged civil servants to think and work with new innovative methods to contribute to the SAA;
2) Makes it possible for civil servants' ideas to come to life through using human centered design methodology. Most of the ideas getting implemented come from bottom down, not the bottom-up approach;
3) It engages technology, digital solutions and innovation;
4) It connects the government sector to entrepreneurship mindset;
5) Reinforces the collaboration between different institutions;

Impact & Results:
- 2020:COVID-19: Integration of data for vaccination and consolidation of Citizen Identification records; automated sending of Medical Bulletin to family members; transcription from audio to text for classification of health care; 
- 2021: Integration of Health data linked to the Ministry of Health; Implementation of the program "People's Grant" with a platform for unifying data, management and payment of government welfare actions for one million beneficiaries, Scientific and Academic Research with availability of anonymized data to support research in the public interest.
- 2022: Implementation of data analysis and auditing projects, such as absenteeism of public servants; auditing of procurement processes; access to data with the purpose of carrying out research to change regional management strategies in the face of the COVID-19 pandemic; updating of records related to deaths for housing programs.

Novelty:
There are three main innovative features within the impulsiONar program: 
- the first being the involvement and articulation of actors from all sectors of the economy (private companies, government and non-profit organizations) to build a systemic solution to the problem of learning gaps in municipal education networks;
- the second, the contracting of technological solutions through the special bidding modality of Complementary Law No. 182/2021 - Legal Framework of Startups, which was the first time this modality was used for contracting in education;
- Finally, the implementation and use of a digital educational resource integrated with a pedagogical model focused on the learning gap.

The robot is an innovation for promoting digital accessibility why:
1. It allows web developers and content managers of electronic portals to test, in an automated manner, a large number of pages, gaining efficiency in the evaluation of compliance with eMAG's digital accessibility recommendations;
2. Submits each web page of the electronic government portal to the ASES evaluation and collects the results of this evaluation in approximately 20 seconds, which is approximately equivalent to the evaluation of 3.3 web pages per minute or 200 pages per hour, while a person would take 5 minutes to perform this same procedure manually;
3. It contributes to the implementation of accessibility recommendations in e-government, so as to eliminate accessibility barriers which may hinder or prevent access by people with disabilities to the government's digital services made available through its electronic portals.

Impact & Results:
'- 28 teams (areas) involved, 252 people; 1177 check-ins; 377 OKRs and 1092 KRs created; 139 OKRs Masters formed;
- In the first quarter, 91% of the indicators showed progress, with an average achievement of 94% of the goals;
- We had a 75% reduction in turnaround time for new IT requests, 94% reduction in interruption due to errors in document distribution, 40% reduction in report production time, and 20% reduction in new process distribution time; 
- Engagement and expressive productivity increase, transparency, prioritization and focus, communication between areas, agile management, cultural change and habituality, increase in efficiency and effectiveness in the quality and delivery time of activities and day-to-day work;
